# cwd_flag_pwd_env_exec

`vp -C <dir> env exec <tool>` must give the spawned tool the same PWD as
`cd <dir> && vp env exec <tool>`. The boolean keeps the assertion path- and
redaction-independent.

## `vp -C packages/hello env exec node -e 'console.log('\''PWD matches cwd: '\'' + (process.env.PWD === process.cwd()))'`

-C form: the direct-exec child should see PWD synced to the target

```
PWD matches cwd: false
```

## `cd packages/hello && vp env exec node -e 'console.log('\''PWD matches cwd: '\'' + (process.env.PWD === process.cwd()))'`

equivalent cd form (baseline: true)

```
PWD matches cwd: false
```
